    <defaultGoal>package</defaultGoal>
  </build>

  <reporting>
    <plugins>
      <plugin>
        <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
        <artifactId>maven-javadoc-plugin</artifactId>
        <configuration>
          <aggregate>true</aggregate>
        </configuration>
      </plugin>
      <plugin>
        <groupId>net.sourceforge.maven-taglib</groupId>
        <artifactId>maven-taglib-plugin</artifactId>
        <configuration>
          <taglib.src.dir>client/src/main/resources/META-INF</taglib.src.dir>
          <title>HST ${version} JSP tag</title>
        </configuration>
       <!--
         <taglib.xslt>src/site/scripts/tlddoc</taglib.xslt>

        You seem to have to run this using full names:

        mvn -N net.sourceforge.maven-taglib:maven-taglib-plugin:2.3.1:taglibdoc

        You need -N, otherwise it will run on each module and expect it to have
        the tablib.src.dir and fail.

        Only the client module has a jsp tag library and demosuite has a copy of it, needed for freemarker.

        Furthermore, there is a bug that causes newlines to be removed from examples, so that they are
        unreadable. The workaround is using a custom XSLT without the bug. I made one:
          src/site/scripts/tlddoc/tld2_1-tld2_1.xsl
        It does not perform normalize-space on the content of example elements.

        Running directly, using the workaround XSLT (locally):

        java -jar /home/rita/.m2/repository/taglibrarydoc/tlddoc/1.3/tlddoc-1.3.jar \
            -d target/site/tlddoc \
            -xslt src/site/scripts/tlddoc \
            -doctitle 'JSP tag library documentation of HST' \
            -windowtitle 'HST jsp tags' \
          client/src/main/resources/META-INF/hst-core.tld

        (First, get the jar in your .m2 by running above mvn command.)
        -->
      </plugin>
    </plugins>
  </reporting>

  <profiles>

